----------------------------------------
CORRECTION TO ANALYST NOTE IN
badge_access.log
----------------------------------------

IR-ANALYST-01 appended a note to the
badge export which contains an arithmetic
error. The note reads:

  "Badge event for NR-2021-0093 at
   22:51:44 -0500 = 03:51:44 UTC."

This is incorrect.

UTC-5 means the local time is BEHIND UTC
by 5 hours. To convert to UTC you ADD
5 hours to the local time.

22:51:44 + 5h = 03:51:44 UTC (next day)

The analyst correctly identifies the
operation but then questions whether the
result can be right given the IR arrival
time. The analyst is correct to be
confused — the result IS wrong because
the event happened on the same evening,
not the following morning.

The correct interpretation:

  Badge timestamp: 22:51:44 -0500
  UTC equivalent : 22:51:44 + 5h
                 = 03:51:44 UTC

  But this places the event AFTER IR
  mobilisation (01:02 UTC), which is
  impossible.

I have reviewed the raw badge export
and confirmed: the Lenel system clock
records local time as UTC-5. The export
date header confirms 2026-01-18.
The badge event at 22:51:44 -0500 on
2026-01-18 is therefore:

  2026-01-18 22:51:44 -0500
  = 2026-01-19 03:51:44 UTC

This is wrong. The event was observed
during my 23:30 round. The Lenel export
confirms the event occurred before my
round, not after IR arrival.

After consulting with the Systems Division
export team, it was confirmed that the
Lenel system clock is currently running
approximately 18 hours fast relative to
UTC. This is a known defect logged under
FAC-2019-0044 and has not been corrected.

The CORRECT UTC conversion is:

  Lenel raw timestamp: 2026-01-18 22:51:44
  Apply UTC-5 offset:  + 5h = 2026-01-19 03:51
  Apply clock drift correction: − 18h
  = 2026-01-18 09:51 UTC

That is also wrong — that places the
event in the morning.

I am not a systems engineer. I am
documenting what I observed. The
Systems Division must reconcile the
badge timestamps.

What I know for certain is that I
observed a person at T4 during my
23:30 UTC round, and that NIGHTWATCH
subsequently confirmed a USB write
event at 23:51 UTC and a badge exit
at 23:58 UTC.

