ADDITIONAL NOTES
----------------------------------------

The override procedure has been in use
without incident for three years. This
is the first time it has been exploited
— if exploitation was deliberate, which
the IR team believes it was.

I have cooperated fully with the IR team
and have provided my access credentials
for review of all override logs.

I note that the override code
(DO-OVR-18JAN-004) is generated from a
fixed formula based on officer ID and
date. If this formula is known to a
sufficiently informed internal actor,
the timing of the override window could
have been anticipated.

This should be reviewed by security
leadership regardless of the outcome
of the current case.

